Egyptian Stocks: EFG-Hermes Holding, Orascom Telecom Decline

-- B y   A h m e d   A   N a m a t a l l a
-- 
2011-06-02T13:37:25Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-02/egyptian-stocks-efg-hermes-holding-orascom-telecom-decline.html
Egypt ’s benchmark EGX 30 Index
declined 2.7 percent, the most since April 18, to 5,361.88 at
the 2:30 p.m. close in Cairo. The gauge dropped 0.9 percent this
week.  The following shares rose or fell in Cairo. Symbols are in
parentheses.  EFG-Hermes Holding SAE (HRHO EY) lost 5.9 percent, the most
since April 18, to 21.13 Egyptian pounds. The country’s biggest
publicly traded investment bank was cut to “neutral” from
“outperform” at Credit Suisse Group AG, which said the recent
increase in the stock price is unlikely to continue in the next
two quarters. The share-price estimate was set at 26 pounds.  Orascom Telecom Holding SAE (ORTE)   fell 2.8 percent to
4.22 pounds, the lowest level since May 18. North Africa’s
biggest mobile-network operator said its wholly owned unit
Telecel Globe agreed to sell its Powercom (Pty) Ltd. subsidiary
in  Namibia  to Ivestec and Nedbank in exchange for the buyers
taking over Powercom’s $60 million of debt.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ahmed A Namatalla in Cairo at 
 anamatalla@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Claudia Maedler at 
 cmaedler@bloomberg.net  